        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. between the ages of 16 and 30;

          2. meet CHR criteria for a psychosis risk syndrome determined by the Structured Interview
             for Prodromal Symptoms (SIPS);

          3. have a Scale of Prodromal Symptoms (SOPS) negative subscale (SOPS-Neg) score of > 11,
             with at least one negative symptom of at least moderate severity (i.e., â‰¥ 3)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. meet criteria for a current or lifetime psychotic disorder;

          2. have an IQ < 70;

          3. a history of seizures or clinically significant neurological disorder that may
             contribute to prodromal symptoms.

          4. have been involved in another treatment study in the past 4 weeks.
